# AI Gym & Fitness Assistant

> A full-stack AI-powered fitness ecosystem — React frontend + FastAPI backend.
---

## What This Project Does

The AI Gym & Fitness Assistant is an all-in-one platform that combines computer vision, machine learning, NLP, and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) into a single unified fitness app. It acts as a smart personal trainer, dietician, motivational companion, and data-driven fitness manager.

---

## Modules

| # | Module | Description |
|---|--------|-------------|
| 1 | **AI Gym Trainer** | Real-time pose detection for squats, left/right bicep curls, and posture analysis using MediaPipe |
| 2 | **AI Dietician** | Personalised diet plans using RAG (ChromaDB) + Gemini LLM with BMI/BMR/TDEE calculation |
| 3 | **Smart Gym Assistant** | Intelligent equipment recommendations based on user workout history |
| 4 | **Habit Tracker** | Daily gym attendance logging with RandomForest ML skip prediction and streak tracking |
| 5 | **Virtual Gym Buddy** | Motivational AI chat companion with VADER + TextBlob sentiment analysis and RAG context |
| 6 | **Performance Analyzer** | Biomechanical motion efficiency scoring with non-linear NumPy scaling |
| 7 | **Gym Recommender** | Weekly workout plan generator using cosine similarity ML across 22 workout templates |
| — | **Interactive Dashboard** | Live aggregated stats from all modules — animated counters, performance rings, habit bars, sentiment visualisation |

---

## Tech Stack

### Frontend
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React 18 + Vite |
| Routing | React Router v6 |
| HTTP | Axios |
| Pose Detection | MediaPipe Pose (loaded via CDN — window.Pose / window.Camera) |
| Styling | Inline styles |

### Backend
| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| API Framework | FastAPI (Python 3.12) |
| Server | Uvicorn with hot reload |
| ORM | SQLAlchemy |
| Database | SQLite (`data/gym_assistant.db`) |
| Vector DB | ChromaDB (RAG for diet + buddy modules) |
| LLM | Google Gemini 2.0 Flash (`google-genai`) |
| ML | scikit-learn — RandomForestClassifier + cosine similarity |
| NLP | VADER Sentiment + TextBlob |
| CV | MediaPipe Pose + OpenCV |
| Cloud Storage | Cloudinary (progress photos) |

---

## Project Structure

```
ai_gym_assistant/
│
├── frontend/
│   ├── index.html                  ← MediaPipe CDN scripts in <head>
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── App.jsx                 ← Router + navigation bar
│   │   └── pages/
│   │       ├── Dashboard.jsx       ← Interactive live dashboard
│   │       ├── Trainer.jsx         ← Module 1 — pose detection
│   │       ├── Dietician.jsx       ← Module 2 — diet planner
│   │       ├── Habit.jsx           ← Module 4 — habit tracker
│   │       ├── Buddy.jsx           ← Module 5 — AI chat
│   │       └── Recommender.jsx     ← Module 7 — workout planner
│   └── package.json
│
└── backend/
    ├── main.py                     ← FastAPI entry + /dashboard endpoint
    ├── database.py                 ← SQLAlchemy models (7 tables)
    ├── .env                        ← API keys (not committed to git)
    ├── requirements.txt
    ├── data/
    │   ├── gym_assistant.db        ← SQLite database (auto-created)
    │   └── workout_log.csv         ← Habit tracker CSV backup
    ├── chroma_db/                  ← ChromaDB vector store (auto-created)
    └── modules/
        ├── __init__.py
        ├── trainer.py              ← Module 1 + habit log + progress photos
        ├── dietician.py            ← Module 2
        ├── equipment.py            ← Module 3
        ├── habit.py                ← Module 4 (frontend routes to /trainer/*)
        ├── buddy.py                ← Module 5
        ├── performance.py          ← Module 6
        └── recommender.py          ← Module 7
```

---

## Database Schema (SQLite — 7 tables)

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `users` | User profile and preferences |
| `workout_sessions` | Rep logs from the Trainer page |
| `habit_logs` | Daily mood, stress, gym attendance |
| `diet_logs` | BMI, BMR, TDEE, calorie targets |
| `chat_history` | FitBot messages + VADER sentiment scores |
| `recommendations` | Generated workout plans (stored as JSON) |
| `progress_photos` | Cloudinary image URLs for progress tracking |

All modules write to SQLite. The Habit ML model re-trains on every prediction call using the full `habit_logs` history — predictions improve as more data is logged.

---

## How to Run

### Requirements
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
- Git

### Backend

```bash
# 1. Navigate to backend
cd backend

# 2. Create and activate virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows
# source venv/bin/activate     # Mac / Linux

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Download TextBlob corpora (one time only)
python -m textblob.download_corpora

# 5. Create .env file with your API keys
# (see API Keys section below)

# 6. Initialise database (auto-runs on first start)
python -c "from database import init_db; init_db()"

# 7. Start server
uvicorn main:app --reload
# Runs on:       http://localhost:8000
# Auto API docs: http://localhost:8000/docs
```

### Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
# Runs on: http://localhost:5173
```

### index.html — Required CDN scripts

These must be in `<head>` of `frontend/index.html` — MediaPipe cannot be imported via npm with Vite:

```html
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/pose@0.5.1675469404/pose.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/camera_utils@0.3.1675466862/camera_utils.js"></script>
```

---

## API Keys Setup

Create `backend/.env` with the following:

```env
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key_here
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret
```

### Getting Keys (all free)

**Gemini API Key:**
1. Go to [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com)
2. Sign in → Get API Key → Copy

**Cloudinary (progress photo storage):**
1. Go to [cloudinary.com](https://cloudinary.com) → Free account
2. Dashboard → copy Cloud Name, API Key, API Secret

