## Setup — Two Terminals Required

---

### Terminal 1 — Backend

```powershell
# 1. Navigate to backend
cd ai_gym_backend

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# 3. Activate — you must see (venv) in prompt before continuing
venv\Scripts\activate

# 4. Install ChromaDB first (pre-built binary — no C++ compiler needed)
pip install chromadb --prefer-binary

# 5. Install all other dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 6. Download TextBlob language data (one time only)
python -m textblob.download_corpora

# 7. Create .env file (see API Keys section below)

# 8. Initialise database
python -c "from database import init_db; init_db()"

# 9. Start backend
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

Backend runs on: `http://localhost:8000`  
API docs at: `http://localhost:8000/docs`

---

### Terminal 2 — Frontend

```powershell
# 1. Navigate to frontend
cd frontend

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Start frontend
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs on: `http://localhost:5173`

---

## API Keys (Both Free)

Create file `ai_gym_backend/.env`:

```env
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=your_cloud_name
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY=your_api_key
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET=your_api_secret
```

**Gemini (free):** https://aistudio.google.com → Get API Key  
**Cloudinary (free — 25GB):** https://cloudinary.com → Dashboard → copy credentials

